Task 2: Data Cleaning & Missing Value Handling
ðŸŽ¯ Objective
The goal of this task is to find missing values in the dataset and clean them using simple methods so that the data quality improves.
ðŸ”¹ Step 1: Import Libraries
Python
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
ðŸ”¹ Step 2: Load the Dataset
(Upload the CSV file first)
Python
df = pd.read_csv("house_prices.csv")
df.head()
ðŸ”¹ Step 3: Check Dataset Details
Python
df.info()
This shows column names, data types, and missing values.
ðŸ”¹ Step 4: Find Missing Values
Python
df.isnull().sum()
This tells how many missing values are present in each column.
ðŸ”¹ Step 5: Show Missing Values Using Graph
Python
df.isnull().sum().plot(kind='bar', figsize=(10,4))
plt.title("Missing Values in Dataset")
plt.show()
ðŸ”¹ Step 6: Save Dataset Size Before Cleaning
Python
before_cleaning = df.shape
before_cleaning
ðŸ”¹ Step 7: Fill Missing Values
âœ” Numerical Columns â†’ Fill with Median
Python
num_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['int64','float64']).columns

for col in num_cols:
    df[col].fillna(df[col].median(), inplace=True)
âœ” Categorical Columns â†’ Fill with Mode
Python
cat_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns

for col in cat_cols:
    df[col].fillna(df[col].mode()[0], inplace=True)
ðŸ”¹ Step 8: Remove Columns with Too Many Missing Values
Python
df = df.dropna(axis=1, thresh=len(df)*0.5)
ðŸ”¹ Step 9: Check Missing Values After Cleaning
Python
df.isnull().sum()
ðŸ”¹ Step 10: Compare Before and After
Python
print("Before Cleaning:", before_cleaning)
print("After Cleaning:", df.shape)
ðŸ”¹ Step 11: Save Cleaned Dataset
Python
df.to_csv("cleaned_house_prices.csv", index=False)
âœ… Final Explanation (Very Simple)
Missing values were identified
Numerical data filled using median
Categorical data filled using mode
Dataset was cleaned successfully
